WEBVTT

00:44.000 --> 00:49.614
[BIRDS CHIRPING]
[WIND WHOOSHING]

00:50.615 --> 00:55.055
[CAR ENGINE RUMBLING]

01:02.366 --> 01:03.541
[CAR ENGINE REVVING]

01:03.628 --> 01:06.979
[MUSIC PLAYING
DISTANTLY OVER RADIO]

01:07.154 --> 01:09.286
Are you sure
we haven't passed the turnoff?

01:09.373 --> 01:11.375
["FAVOURITE PEOPLE"
PLAYING OVER RADIO] LILY: Yeah, I think so.

01:11.506 --> 01:13.377
She said the turn should be
coming up here pretty quick.

01:13.508 --> 01:15.901
<i>♪ Call me a diamond </i>
<i>But don't tell me to shine ♪</i>

01:19.122 --> 01:22.125
<i>♪ Straight lines </i>
<i>Oh, oh, oh! ♪</i>

01:22.343 --> 01:23.387
Oh, wait, wait, wait!

01:27.522 --> 01:29.219
I... think you just passed it.

01:31.874 --> 01:35.182
[SCOFFS] Lily, there's no way
that leads to a campground.

01:35.791 --> 01:36.748
Please.

01:37.227 --> 01:39.229
[SCOFFS] Okay.

01:40.665 --> 01:42.798
You are the boss.
[CHUCKLES]

01:43.059 --> 01:45.366
<i>♪ All she ever talks about</i>
<i>Is making it last... ♪</i>

01:52.895 --> 01:56.681
This is so nice. [CHUCKLES]
I think I see a lake.

01:57.552 --> 01:58.944
Oh, yeah. Look at that.

01:59.075 --> 02:00.729
<i>♪ Made of glass ♪</i>

02:00.816 --> 02:06.038
<i>♪ Rihanna feels like she's </i>
<i>The only girl in the world ♪</i>

02:06.474 --> 02:07.605
<i>♪ She wants you to stay ♪</i>

02:07.910 --> 02:11.174
<i>♪ There's too much riding</i>
<i>On nothing diamonds ♪</i>

02:11.305 --> 02:12.523
<i>♪ I gotta get outta here... ♪</i>

02:12.610 --> 02:16.440
[BRANDON LAUGHING]
LILY: Oh, my gosh!

02:16.527 --> 02:18.138
It's beautiful.

02:18.660 --> 02:19.922
[SONG STOPS PLAYING]

02:23.143 --> 02:24.274
[BIRD CAWING]

02:24.361 --> 02:26.233
[LAUGHS][LAUGHS] Let's go.

02:26.320 --> 02:29.061
[PANTS, CHUCKLES]

02:29.714 --> 02:31.977
BRANDON: Whoo-hoo!

02:32.064 --> 02:33.936
[BOTH CHUCKLE]

02:34.023 --> 02:35.938
BRANDON: Oh, it's perfect.

02:36.547 --> 02:38.158
[WHISPERING] Wow, yeah.

02:41.813 --> 02:45.121
[IN NORMAL VOICE]
And just like that woman said, there's no one even here.

02:45.208 --> 02:47.428
BRANDON: Come on.
[LILY CHUCKLES]

02:47.602 --> 02:49.256
BRANDON:
Where do you wanna set up?

02:49.343 --> 02:51.083
LILY: I don't actually
wanna set up yet.

02:51.171 --> 02:52.998
BRANDON: What do you mean?
This place is fucking great.

02:53.085 --> 02:54.043
LILY: I know...

02:55.349 --> 02:57.916
I didn't mean
I didn't wanna stay here.

02:58.003 --> 03:01.311
I just meant
that I don't wanna set up yet.

03:02.094 --> 03:03.052
Hmm.

03:04.227 --> 03:05.402
What'd you have in mind?

03:05.881 --> 03:06.925
Hmm...

03:08.144 --> 03:09.667
I don't know...

03:11.278 --> 03:12.453
[BREATHES DEEPLY]

03:12.540 --> 03:14.281
[BOTH SMOOCHES]

03:18.023 --> 03:20.069
[BOTH CHUCKLE]

03:20.200 --> 03:21.679
[KISSES]

03:21.766 --> 03:23.377
[GASPS] Oh! Oh, my god.

03:23.464 --> 03:24.595
[CHUCKLES]
What? What is it?

03:25.074 --> 03:26.467
I guess people are here.

03:28.251 --> 03:29.252
BRANDON: Shit.

03:29.426 --> 03:31.472
[SCOFFS]
[CLEARS THROAT]

03:31.559 --> 03:33.343
[TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

03:33.430 --> 03:34.518
Hello.

03:35.476 --> 03:38.043
What the fuck? Hold on.
[HESITATES] Why is he... why is he coming?

03:39.175 --> 03:40.394
Hey, uh... [CHUCKLES]

03:41.177 --> 03:42.265
...can I help you
with something?

03:42.396 --> 03:44.136
Brandon... Brandon.
Just... just ignore them.

03:44.224 --> 03:46.051
It's fine, we can set up
and get back to that later.

03:46.138 --> 03:47.401
No, this is...
this is messed up. Hey!

03:47.836 --> 03:49.185
[SCOFFS] How about
a little privacy here, huh?

03:49.664 --> 03:51.056
Whoa, whoa, whoa.
What the fuck, man?

03:51.143 --> 03:53.363
[DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYING]
[PANTS]

03:53.450 --> 03:55.974
[PROWLERS GRUNT]
[GASPS, SCREAMS] No! Brandon!

03:56.061 --> 03:58.020
No! [GROANS]
[LILY GASPING]

03:58.150 --> 04:00.196
[SOBS] No!
Lily!

04:00.283 --> 04:01.893
[PROWLER GRUNTS]
Brandon!

04:01.980 --> 04:04.287
[MUSIC CONCLUDES]

04:05.375 --> 04:09.945
["ARROWS TO FLOWERS" PLAYING]

04:10.075 --> 04:13.775
[PLAYERS SHOUTING, CLAMORING]

04:13.862 --> 04:15.646
<i>♪ Oh, baby, love ♪</i>

04:15.733 --> 04:17.866
Yes! Nice pass, Alex.

04:17.953 --> 04:21.086
[SCATTERED CROWD APPLAUSE]
[LIVELY CHATTER]

04:21.173 --> 04:23.219
<i>♪ I don't want no... ♪</i>

04:23.350 --> 04:26.048
[SUPPORTERS EXCLAIMING,
CHATTERING INDISTINCTLY]

04:26.135 --> 04:27.963
[SONG CONCLUDES]

04:28.180 --> 04:29.181
[WHISTLE BLOWING]

04:29.617 --> 04:33.229
[SOMBER MUSIC PLAYING]
[CROWD CHEERING, APPLAUDING]

04:33.795 --> 04:35.275
PLAYER: That was so cool!

04:35.753 --> 04:38.626
[INDISTINCT CHATTER]

04:39.104 --> 04:40.280
[SCOFFS]
[WHISTLE BLOWING]

04:41.193 --> 04:43.631
[CROWD CHEERING, APPLAUDING]

04:45.459 --> 04:46.416
Always the hero.

04:47.852 --> 04:49.550
Glad you could make it, Danny.

04:49.854 --> 04:51.508
You seem surprised.

04:51.726 --> 04:54.468
No, I'm just glad
some mission didn't come up

04:54.555 --> 04:56.078
that prevented you
from being here.

04:56.208 --> 04:58.080
What could be more important
than taking my daughter

04:58.167 --> 04:59.342
to visit a few colleges?

04:59.429 --> 05:00.474
[WHISTLE BLOWING]

05:00.648 --> 05:02.824
I really do appreciate
you agreeing to take her

05:02.954 --> 05:03.868
on such short notice.

05:04.434 --> 05:05.522
I'm happy to do it.

05:06.393 --> 05:08.177
Just kinda surprised
you don't wanna take her.

05:08.264 --> 05:09.787
I do. But...

05:10.397 --> 05:11.702
The hospital changed my schedule

05:11.789 --> 05:13.965
and I can't afford
to take that many days off.

05:15.227 --> 05:16.838
And given that she and I
have been butting heads

05:16.925 --> 05:17.882
about things lately,

05:18.361 --> 05:19.884
I honestly thought
it'd be better if you took her.

05:21.625 --> 05:23.453
You've been away a lot
these past couple years.

05:23.540 --> 05:24.411
Hmm.

05:24.846 --> 05:26.195
You don't have a lot of time
to reconnect with her

05:26.326 --> 05:27.849
before she goes to college.

05:29.633 --> 05:31.113
How does she feel about it?

05:33.289 --> 05:34.421
Yeah...

05:35.770 --> 05:38.468
[CROWD EXCLAIMING, CHEERING]
Nice shot, Alex!

05:38.599 --> 05:42.864
[PLAYERS CHEERING]

05:43.343 --> 05:44.605
That's why I'm glad
you reached out.

05:44.996 --> 05:47.129
I'm just surprised
you have this much time off.

05:48.652 --> 05:51.612
Actually... I retired.

05:53.614 --> 05:56.356
What? [SCOFFS]
[PENSIVE MUSIC PLAYING]

05:56.443 --> 05:58.358
I thought
you were gonna do 30 years.

05:59.141 --> 06:00.229
So did I.

06:01.404 --> 06:03.711
Then they tried
to put me on a desk, and...

06:04.451 --> 06:05.539
it's just not me.

06:07.454 --> 06:08.803
That's the whole reason?

06:09.369 --> 06:10.282
Yeah.

06:11.022 --> 06:13.677
I mean, the ride lasted longer
than it probably should've.

06:15.026 --> 06:16.506
I missed out on a lot.

06:19.988 --> 06:21.381
What are you gonna do now?

06:21.816 --> 06:24.166
Long term? I have no idea.

06:25.080 --> 06:28.039
But right now, I'm just focused
on these college visits

06:28.605 --> 06:30.259
and trying not to make things
worse with her.

06:30.738 --> 06:31.695
JANINE: Hmm.

06:32.392 --> 06:34.002
[WHISTLE BLOWING]
[MUSIC CONCLUDES]

06:35.220 --> 06:37.832
[CAR ENGINE RUMBLING]

06:38.441 --> 06:42.271
[BIRDS CHIRPING]

06:50.148 --> 06:52.107
[KEYS JANGLING]
[CAR ENGINE STOPS]

06:53.891 --> 06:57.504
[INDISTINCT CHATTER]

06:57.939 --> 06:58.853
Hey.
DANIEL: Hey.

06:58.983 --> 07:00.463
Alex!
ALEX: Coming.

07:04.206 --> 07:05.686
There's our soccer star.

07:06.730 --> 07:07.688
Hey, Daniel.

07:08.123 --> 07:09.080
Hi.

07:10.081 --> 07:10.952
JANINE: All right, I think

07:11.343 --> 07:12.693
I should get a picture
of you two before you go.

07:12.780 --> 07:13.737
ALEX: I got it.

07:16.436 --> 07:18.699
Alex, let's just get
a... a shot.

07:19.134 --> 07:20.831
Mom.
No, come on. It'll be quick.

07:20.918 --> 07:21.745
Just get closer.

07:23.094 --> 07:26.271
Oh, come on, closer than that.
[CHUCKLES] Come on. Smile!

07:26.358 --> 07:27.403
[CHUCKLES]

07:27.490 --> 07:29.187
[CAMERA SHUTTER CLICKING]
[CHUCKLES]

07:29.274 --> 07:31.146
Not bad. Okay. Uh...
Yeah.

07:31.973 --> 07:33.409
Just call me every day.
Yes.

07:33.496 --> 07:35.324
JANINE: I love you.
I love you too. Bye.

07:38.588 --> 07:40.503
Okay. Please make sure
she calls every day.

07:40.590 --> 07:42.244
I will pick up,
even if I'm on shift.

07:42.331 --> 07:43.332
Of course.

07:43.506 --> 07:45.813
She may not act like it now,
but one day...

07:45.943 --> 07:47.249
she will appreciate this.

07:51.427 --> 07:53.951
Better get moving.
JANINE: Yeah. Okay. Um...

07:54.125 --> 07:56.693
Have a good time, you two.
Be safe. Danny.

07:58.521 --> 08:00.480
Take care of her.
I will.

08:00.567 --> 08:02.003
["TONIGHT" PLAYING]

08:02.482 --> 08:05.006
Okay. Bye. Love you.
Bye. Love you.

08:06.790 --> 08:08.183
So, we're doing this.

08:08.662 --> 08:12.274
It's exciting.
Yeah. Totally.

08:19.324 --> 08:22.327
<i>♪ You didn't have to tell me </i>

08:23.285 --> 08:25.722
<i>♪ I already knew </i>

08:26.854 --> 08:30.945
<i>♪ That I had my life backwards </i>

08:31.032 --> 08:32.773
<i>♪ An illusion to choose ♪</i>

08:32.860 --> 08:33.687
[LAUGHS]

08:35.297 --> 08:40.345
<i>♪ I’m trading in my brass ring </i>
<i>Maybe now I’ll find some luck ♪</i>

08:42.565 --> 08:46.482
<i>♪ A moment on my hands</i>
<i>Forever prayer ♪</i>

08:46.569 --> 08:48.702
<i>♪ Forever lost ♪</i>

08:50.834 --> 08:52.488
<i>♪ Such a shame </i>

08:53.968 --> 08:56.361
<i>♪ What a thing to choose </i>

08:58.059 --> 09:00.844
<i>♪ I’m out on the gallows ♪</i>

09:01.889 --> 09:07.808
<i>♪ But you’re gonna save me ♪</i>

09:09.505 --> 09:12.769
[SONG CONCLUDES]
[CAR ENGINE STOPS]

09:17.121 --> 09:19.341
[INDISTINCT CHATTER
OVER CELL PHONE]

09:19.428 --> 09:20.951
Yo.
ALEX: Huh?

09:22.083 --> 09:23.040
Wanna use the bathroom?

09:23.171 --> 09:26.000
Oh, no. I'm good.
[BREATHES DEEPLY]

09:26.087 --> 09:29.090
[UPBEAT MUSIC PLAYING
OVER EARPODS]

09:39.013 --> 09:40.144
[KEYPAD BEEPS]

09:41.189 --> 09:44.235
[GAS PUMP CLANKING, WHIRRING]

09:53.636 --> 09:54.985
What are you watching
over there?

09:55.333 --> 09:56.987
Nothing. Just stupid stuff.

09:57.118 --> 10:00.382
Like what? Like cats
ice skating or something?

10:00.991 --> 10:03.254
Cats ice skating?
Is that a thing?

10:03.603 --> 10:05.779
DANIEL: On there,
everything's a thing, isn't it?

10:07.302 --> 10:10.218
When I was overseas,
if we had Internet,

10:10.305 --> 10:12.220
I'd spend hours
watching that junk.

10:12.307 --> 10:14.265
Oh, you had Internet. Hmm.

10:15.223 --> 10:16.311
Must've been some other reason

10:16.398 --> 10:18.139
why I barely heard
from you then.

10:18.705 --> 10:20.489
Let me guess.
Operational security.

10:20.576 --> 10:22.012
DANIEL: Yeah, we take
that kinda thing... Yeah.

10:22.230 --> 10:23.361
...seriously in a combat zone.

10:23.448 --> 10:24.580
Good. Good.

10:25.059 --> 10:26.669
No, 'cause I was just starting
to think you didn't care, but...

10:26.756 --> 10:29.150
Alex, come on, you know
I didn't have a choice.

10:29.541 --> 10:32.327
Technically, it is a choice
to join the army.

10:32.675 --> 10:35.373
So... yeah, you kinda did.

10:35.460 --> 10:37.811
DANIEL: Alex, I was a soldier.
Yeah, I know.

10:37.898 --> 10:40.552
DANIEL: And it's not just
what I did, it's who I was.

10:40.640 --> 10:42.685
It's what I felt like
I was called to do.

10:44.992 --> 10:47.734
And I am sorry that it took me
away from you and your mom.

10:47.864 --> 10:50.606
But you loved it,
and you'd do it again, right?

10:52.129 --> 10:52.956
Wouldn't you?

10:55.263 --> 10:56.177
Yeah. [CHUCKLES] Okay.

10:56.438 --> 10:57.744
You know what?
I am gonna use the bathroom.

10:57.831 --> 11:02.487
[SCOFFS, SIGHS]
[SOLEMN MUSIC PLAYING]

11:03.706 --> 11:05.969
You're carrying. Right?
Of course I am.

11:07.188 --> 11:08.406
Right. Well, put it away.

11:10.321 --> 11:11.801
What?
Lock it up.

11:11.932 --> 11:13.411
Alex, I am a highly-trained
soldier, I was--

11:13.542 --> 11:16.110
God forbid someone actually
sees you with that thing

11:16.197 --> 11:17.938
and thinks I'm a redneck
or something.

11:18.068 --> 11:19.591
You shouldn't care
about what people think.

11:19.679 --> 11:22.246
Look, if you can't even do
this one thing for me, it's...

11:22.333 --> 11:23.987
it’s okay. Mom can pick me up.

11:24.074 --> 11:27.251
[BREATHES DEEPLY]
ALEX: It’s really not that far.

11:27.382 --> 11:30.428
[GRUNTS SOFTLY]
[SOLEMN MUSIC BUILDS]

11:30.820 --> 11:31.691
Close your door.

11:47.794 --> 11:50.361
[KEYS JANGLING]

11:52.755 --> 11:53.625
There.

11:54.801 --> 11:55.715
We good?

11:56.759 --> 11:57.804
Thank you, Daniel.

11:58.195 --> 12:00.067
You know, if you're not going
to call me Dad,

12:00.154 --> 12:01.155
you could at least...

12:01.242 --> 12:02.373
[MUSIC CONCLUDES]

12:02.460 --> 12:04.593
DANIEL: You could at least
call me Danny.

12:05.463 --> 12:06.856
My mom called me Daniel.

12:06.943 --> 12:10.207
[UPBEAT MUSIC
PLAYING OVER RADIO]

12:10.338 --> 12:11.208
[INDISTINCT CHATTER]

12:11.295 --> 12:13.297
ALEX: Thank you.
DANIEL: Thanks.

12:16.605 --> 12:19.564
It seems like
there's a dress code. If you're too embarrassed

12:19.651 --> 12:21.566
to be seen, you can just wait
in the truck, you know?

12:21.653 --> 12:23.917
No, I wanna go
to the parents thing.

12:24.700 --> 12:26.136
See what this place
is all about.

12:26.310 --> 12:27.224
Okay.

12:27.529 --> 12:29.183
Just so you know,
all you have to do is

12:29.270 --> 12:30.750
bring back any forms
they give you

12:30.837 --> 12:32.403
and say that
this is my top choice.

12:32.490 --> 12:33.404
Is it?

12:35.015 --> 12:36.538
I just need you to say it is.

12:37.931 --> 12:38.845
Okay.

12:43.632 --> 12:45.329
Thanks.
I'll see you after. Okay?

12:45.416 --> 12:46.287
DANIEL: Copy.

12:47.897 --> 12:53.250
[MAJESTIC CHORAL MUSIC PLAYING]
[CHOIR VOCALIZING]

13:12.182 --> 13:13.314
[SIGHS]

13:20.800 --> 13:21.931
DIRECTOR: Hello, everyone.

13:22.062 --> 13:24.194
Thank you so much
for joining us this afternoon.

13:24.281 --> 13:25.979
As we go around,
please let us know

13:26.066 --> 13:27.850
what your child's
favorite subject is,

13:27.937 --> 13:30.200
what major
they intend to pursue,

13:30.287 --> 13:33.421
and any activities
or hobbies they're into.

13:33.551 --> 13:36.337
Um, we'll start with you, sir.
In the flannel shirt.

13:41.255 --> 13:42.169
Uh, yeah.

13:43.561 --> 13:45.041
My daughter is Alex Beckett.

13:45.999 --> 13:48.001
DIRECTOR: Mm-hmm.
She plays soccer.

13:48.740 --> 13:49.611
Hmm.

13:50.394 --> 13:51.700
And I think she's...

13:52.570 --> 13:55.617
pretty good at math
and reading...

13:56.357 --> 13:58.838
science, you know,
all the subjects, really.

13:59.142 --> 14:01.841
Do you know if she has
a particular major in mind?

14:03.712 --> 14:04.844
Uh...

14:05.714 --> 14:07.150
She's into a lot of things.

14:07.237 --> 14:08.586
[CHUCKLES]

14:10.980 --> 14:12.460
But I do know
that this university

14:12.547 --> 14:13.896
is her first choice.

14:14.505 --> 14:16.377
I see, um, just to be clear,

14:16.464 --> 14:18.640
this is a college,
not a university.

14:18.727 --> 14:19.597
There's a difference.

14:20.642 --> 14:21.904
And what about you, ma'am?

14:22.078 --> 14:24.733
[INDISTINCT CHATTER]

14:25.516 --> 14:27.867
So, how'd it go?
ALEX: It was fine.

14:28.911 --> 14:31.044
Can we go?
Sure.

14:31.131 --> 14:33.873
[BIRDS CHIRPING]
[INDISTINCT CHATTER]

14:36.571 --> 14:37.572
Hey.

14:37.833 --> 14:39.879
So, what is your favorite
class at school?

14:40.488 --> 14:41.358
Why?

14:42.577 --> 14:45.623
Turns out, I'm expected to know
something about your academics.

14:46.276 --> 14:47.582
And what you wanna study.

14:48.409 --> 14:50.237
Well, I can just
forward you my transcript.

14:51.455 --> 14:53.240
Or we could have a conversation.

14:56.634 --> 14:58.506
[CELLPHONE BLIPS]
Just sent it to you.

14:58.593 --> 15:00.160
[CELLPHONE BUZZING, CHIMING]

15:02.031 --> 15:03.467
Can't wait to check 'em out.

15:11.519 --> 15:12.694
DANIEL: Really?

15:13.216 --> 15:15.218
Well, then I will be
on my best behavior.

15:15.305 --> 15:16.872
[INDISTINCT CHATTER]

15:16.959 --> 15:18.613
DANIEL: Yeah.
Yeah, she's right here.

15:19.919 --> 15:20.832
Wanna talk to your mom?

15:21.137 --> 15:23.226
Hey, Mom. It's going great.
Love you. Bye.

15:25.968 --> 15:27.143
Uh-huh, yeah.

15:28.579 --> 15:31.452
Okay. We will call you
after the visit tomorrow.

15:31.974 --> 15:32.888
Bye.

15:33.280 --> 15:34.411
[CELLPHONE BEEPS]
What'd she want?

15:35.760 --> 15:37.023
She wanted to let me know

15:37.110 --> 15:38.633
that the school
we're visiting tomorrow

15:38.720 --> 15:40.722
has a scholarship
offer on the table.

15:41.244 --> 15:43.420
And to make sure you connect
with the soccer coach.

15:43.507 --> 15:44.378
Yeah.

15:46.597 --> 15:48.338
What's wrong?
Nothing. No.

15:48.817 --> 15:50.514
It's just weird
that she thinks I'd forget

15:50.601 --> 15:51.994
to connect
with the soccer coach.

15:52.212 --> 15:55.650
I don't know, seems like a...
normal motherly reminder to me.

15:55.911 --> 15:57.130
ALEX: No, it is, it is.

15:58.000 --> 15:59.741
It's just, all she's been
wanting to talk about lately

15:59.828 --> 16:00.742
is soccer.

16:01.047 --> 16:02.962
Don't you like soccer?
ALEX: Yeah, sure.

16:03.049 --> 16:04.267
I mean, I'm happy

16:04.398 --> 16:06.008
about the scholarship offers
we're getting.

16:06.095 --> 16:08.054
Like, I know
it'll help financially, but...

16:10.143 --> 16:11.144
Honestly, I don't even know

16:11.231 --> 16:12.449
if I like playing soccer
that much.

16:13.015 --> 16:15.104
And then playing it in college
is gonna take up

16:15.191 --> 16:18.281
so much of my time, and...
there's other things I...

16:18.934 --> 16:20.675
I don't know, I'm...
I'm into a lot more.

16:20.762 --> 16:21.632
Really?

16:22.590 --> 16:23.547
Like what?

16:25.462 --> 16:26.333
Art?

16:28.683 --> 16:29.727
What makes you say that?

16:30.946 --> 16:32.774
Well, I did look
at your transcripts,

16:32.861 --> 16:35.690
and I saw that you took
an art elective every semester.

16:36.604 --> 16:38.693
It's way more
than what's required, so...

16:39.607 --> 16:41.087
must mean you really like it.

16:42.784 --> 16:43.698
Yeah, I do.

16:44.481 --> 16:46.048
You wanna tell me more about it?

16:49.704 --> 16:50.922
No, not really.

16:51.053 --> 16:52.968
I don't necessarily
feel like faking

16:53.055 --> 16:54.926
a deep conversation
with you right now.

16:55.014 --> 16:56.450
DANIEL: Alex,
it doesn't have to be

16:56.537 --> 16:58.191
faking a conversation.

16:58.278 --> 17:01.672
If art's what you're into,
I wanna hear all about it.

17:02.456 --> 17:03.848
No, honestly,
I'm just really exhausted.

17:03.935 --> 17:05.807
I should probably
get some sleep, and...

17:05.894 --> 17:07.591
it's a long day tomorrow,
you know?

17:11.726 --> 17:15.338
[SOLEMN MUSIC PLAYING]

17:16.774 --> 17:21.214
[DOOR LOCK CLICKS]

17:21.736 --> 17:23.172
Good night.
ALEX: Good night.

17:34.531 --> 17:38.709
[DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYING]

17:40.972 --> 17:45.673
[RESIDENTS CLAMORING]
MIDWIFE 1: One more push! One more push!

17:46.152 --> 17:49.285
Go. Go. Yes! Push!
MIDWIFE 2: Breathe. Big push.

17:49.372 --> 17:52.462
[INDISTINCT CHATTER]
MIDWIFE 2: Big push, you can do this.

17:53.637 --> 17:55.944
I'm sorry. I'm so sorry.

17:58.816 --> 18:01.254
MOTHER: [SOBBING]
My baby! My baby!

18:05.910 --> 18:09.218
ABIGAIL: That's the fifth one.
Something wrong with the girls.

18:13.048 --> 18:17.661
[MUSIC CONCLUDES]
[INDISTINCT CHATTER]

18:17.748 --> 18:19.054
ALEX: Bye.
Bye, Alex.

18:20.925 --> 18:24.407
[DISTANT CHURCH BELL TOLLING]

18:24.886 --> 18:27.454
DANIEL: How'd it go?
It was fine. I don't know.

18:27.541 --> 18:29.760
Place seems like
a really big party school.

18:29.847 --> 18:31.327
DANIEL: Yeah, I did see
they have a thing here

18:31.458 --> 18:33.024
called the freshman
underwear run.

18:33.112 --> 18:35.853
[LAUGHS] Yeah, I don't know.
I'm not really into it.

18:36.506 --> 18:38.204
Well, we got two more
to see, right?

18:38.769 --> 18:39.640
Yeah.

18:41.642 --> 18:42.599
What's wrong?

18:42.947 --> 18:44.427
I just-- I don't know
if I really wanna see

18:44.514 --> 18:45.863
the other two schools.

18:46.995 --> 18:47.865
Okay.

18:50.433 --> 18:52.566
Can I ask you something?
Yeah.

18:53.958 --> 18:55.308
So, I emailed this school

18:55.395 --> 18:56.526
that I'm interested in
last night,

18:56.613 --> 18:57.875
and they got back to me,

18:58.049 --> 19:00.313
and they said they can
fit me in for a tour tomorrow.

19:02.184 --> 19:03.098
Can you take me?

19:05.013 --> 19:06.014
What school is it?

19:06.884 --> 19:08.016
It's an arts school.

19:09.278 --> 19:11.019
ALEX: I really wanna try to see

19:11.106 --> 19:12.629
if there's, like,
a future in it for me and...

19:13.500 --> 19:14.370
You know?

19:15.023 --> 19:17.243
But if... if you're not into it,
then obviously, you know...

19:17.373 --> 19:18.766
DANIEL: Well, I'm into it.

19:19.636 --> 19:21.986
It's, like, a nine-hour drive
the other way though.

19:23.945 --> 19:26.774
I'm retired.
Got nothing but time.

19:27.688 --> 19:28.689
Wait. No.

19:29.864 --> 19:30.778
Are you serious?

19:31.257 --> 19:34.085
Yeah.
[LAUGHS] Okay. Okay.

19:36.566 --> 19:37.567
Um...

19:37.654 --> 19:40.657
[TENDER MUSIC PLAYING]

19:40.744 --> 19:43.007
There's just
one other thing. Um...

19:44.226 --> 19:45.619
Can you not tell Mom about it?
[SIGHS]

19:45.793 --> 19:47.621
ALEX: I swear I'll tell her
once we get home and... and--

19:47.708 --> 19:50.537
Alex, that's--
I'll say I made you do it. You know, it's my fault.

19:51.755 --> 19:55.585
Look, she just has this idea
of... of my future in her head,

19:55.716 --> 19:56.891
and that's not me.

20:00.329 --> 20:04.203
[INHALES, SIGHS]
Where are we headed?

20:04.986 --> 20:06.379
[CHUCKLES]

20:06.466 --> 20:10.165
["BLOOM" PLAYING]

20:13.342 --> 20:15.605
Okay. Thanks.

20:16.824 --> 20:18.869
No... no vacancy
at that one either.

20:20.480 --> 20:22.133
Well, I'm sure
we'll find something.

20:22.221 --> 20:24.527
Just might be a little farther
from the college.

20:24.614 --> 20:25.615
ALEX: That's fine.

20:26.747 --> 20:28.836
<i>♪ Doing everything I can... </i>

20:28.923 --> 20:31.404
You know, if worse
comes to worse...

20:31.534 --> 20:32.927
I do have a tent in the back.

20:33.406 --> 20:34.276
Why?

20:35.016 --> 20:40.282
I got a lotta stuff back there.
I'm just saying, if we had to...

20:41.327 --> 20:42.937
we could do
one night of camping.

20:43.677 --> 20:45.809
Camping?
Yeah, like we used to.

20:45.896 --> 20:48.290
[HESITATES] Okay, I'm going
to keep looking for a hotel.

20:48.421 --> 20:49.726
[CELLPHONE KEYPAD TAPPING]

20:49.857 --> 20:53.077
<i>♪ Feel the sun</i>
<i>On your face ♪</i>

20:53.164 --> 20:56.342
<i>♪ Full of color ♪</i>

20:57.125 --> 21:00.694
<i>♪ I'm in bloom... </i>

21:00.824 --> 21:01.869
[SONG CONCLUDES]

21:02.130 --> 21:04.611
[GROANS] God.

21:04.698 --> 21:07.483
Okay, I just lost my last bar
so that's that.

21:07.570 --> 21:09.659
[SCOFFS] Oh, come on.
[SIGHS]

21:09.746 --> 21:11.922
No service
isn't the end of the world.

21:14.882 --> 21:16.884
Maybe we could even
have a conversation.

21:19.060 --> 21:20.888
[SIGHS] Okay.

21:22.759 --> 21:24.457
What do you want
to talk about? [EXHALES]

21:26.067 --> 21:28.461
Let's talk about...

21:29.026 --> 21:30.158
why looking at an Art college

21:30.245 --> 21:32.116
has to be a secret
from your mom.

21:33.422 --> 21:36.164
Because according to her,
there's no future or money

21:36.251 --> 21:38.819
in drawing or painting.

21:39.950 --> 21:41.561
She just wants you to be happy.

21:43.302 --> 21:44.607
Maybe...

21:45.347 --> 21:46.653
try being honest with her.

21:48.307 --> 21:50.526
Like you're being honest
about your retirement?

21:52.180 --> 21:53.137
What do you mean?

21:53.747 --> 21:56.619
All you ever talked about
was how much you loved the army,

21:56.706 --> 21:57.794
and how you'd wear the uniform

21:57.881 --> 21:59.143
until they ripped it
off your back,

21:59.230 --> 22:00.971
and now you just expect me
to believe

22:01.058 --> 22:03.496
that you decided to retire?

22:03.713 --> 22:06.237
[BREATHES DEEPLY]

22:10.894 --> 22:13.201
Okay. Good talk.

22:13.506 --> 22:16.552
[PENSIVE MUSIC PLAYING]

22:33.090 --> 22:35.397
[MUSIC CONCLUDES]
[CAR ENGINE STALLS]

22:36.180 --> 22:37.660
I'm gonna go use the bathroom.

22:38.052 --> 22:41.185
[DOG BARKING IN THE DISTANCE]
[CAR DOOR CLOSING]

22:41.272 --> 22:43.405
[BIRDS CHIRPING]

22:44.928 --> 22:46.582
[GAS PUMP CLANKING]

22:48.976 --> 22:52.458
["YOU TOOK MY HEART"
PLAYING FAINTLY OVER SPEAKERS]

22:52.588 --> 22:55.417
[REFRIGERATOR WHIRRING]
[CLOCK TICKING]

22:59.682 --> 23:04.905
<i>♪ You took my heart</i>
<i>And bailed away ♪</i>

23:04.992 --> 23:10.084
<i>♪ You wanted me</i>
<i>To take your hand ♪</i>

23:10.301 --> 23:14.828
<i>♪ I knew that you could</i>
<i>Not be changed... ♪</i>

23:15.089 --> 23:16.046
ABIGAIL: You like the art?

23:16.133 --> 23:17.570
[OMINOUS MUSIC PLAYING]

23:17.657 --> 23:20.355
[BREATHES HEAVILY]
Yeah. It's cool.

23:22.618 --> 23:23.576
You wanna buy one?

23:24.794 --> 23:28.407
Uh, no. No, thank you.
Do you have a bathroom?

23:30.626 --> 23:34.413
Yeah. Through that side door.
It's real easy to find.

23:35.065 --> 23:35.936
Thank you.

23:44.074 --> 23:46.207
[MUSIC CONCLUDES]

23:46.686 --> 23:49.819
[CROWS CAWING]

23:53.127 --> 23:56.652
["YOU TOOK MY HEART"
CONTINUES OVER SPEAKERS]

23:56.739 --> 23:58.741
[BOTTLES CLINKING]

24:08.098 --> 24:10.710
[MENACING MUSIC PLAYING]

24:10.797 --> 24:13.626
RESIDENT: Hey. Hey!
[ALEX GRUNTS]

24:14.627 --> 24:16.803
What are you, 16?

24:18.282 --> 24:19.501
Seventeen?

24:21.242 --> 24:22.591
[BREATHES SHAKILY]

24:23.679 --> 24:25.681
[MUSIC CONCLUDES]
[DOOR SLAMS SHUT]

24:26.552 --> 24:27.814
ABIGAIL: Is that it,
plus the gas?

24:27.901 --> 24:28.945
Yep.

24:29.076 --> 24:30.120
Where you headed?
[REGISTER BEEPING]

24:30.338 --> 24:31.818
DANIEL: Well, we're driving
up to Port Winston,

24:32.296 --> 24:35.082
but we were hoping to find
a place to stay near here.

24:35.386 --> 24:36.344
You know of anything?

24:36.997 --> 24:39.216
Nah, there ain't any hotels
between here and Port Winston.

24:39.434 --> 24:40.435
Nothing, huh?

24:40.522 --> 24:41.958
Oh, there's a bunch
of campgrounds

24:42.045 --> 24:43.090
between here and there.

24:43.786 --> 24:46.876
Actually, got a real nice one.
Not too far from here.

24:47.224 --> 24:48.399
How far are we talking?

24:48.487 --> 24:50.053
ABIGAIL: Just a few miles
up the road.

24:50.140 --> 24:51.707
But it's real easy to miss.

24:51.794 --> 24:53.143
Probably best
if I draw you a map.

24:53.622 --> 24:55.624
DANIEL: Thanks. I'm gonna grab
a couple more things.

24:55.711 --> 24:56.582
Mm-hmm.

24:56.669 --> 24:59.019
[WELDER CRACKLING]

25:06.287 --> 25:08.724
["I WISH YOU WERE
WITH ME TONIGHT" PLAYING]

25:08.811 --> 25:11.379
ABIGAIL: There's a small sign
right at the turnoff.

25:11.466 --> 25:13.512
But you wanna go slow
or you're gonna fly right by it.

25:14.295 --> 25:17.820
You wanna make the turn,
and then it's just one mile

25:17.907 --> 25:19.082
from that point.

25:22.738 --> 25:24.261
I got us directions
for a campground.

25:24.348 --> 25:25.349
Okay.

25:25.436 --> 25:26.742
ABIGAIL:
You're gonna love the place.

25:26.960 --> 25:29.310
It's beautiful, and you should
have it all to yourselves.

25:29.876 --> 25:32.008
Hot dogs, chips, water.
Mm-hmm.

25:32.356 --> 25:34.489
Anything else?
No. I'm good. Can we go?

25:34.794 --> 25:36.273
Are you okay?
Yeah, I'm fine.

25:36.360 --> 25:38.406
I just wanna... I just wanna go.

25:38.841 --> 25:39.842
Seventy-eight.

25:41.844 --> 25:44.891
Thanks again,
and keep the change.

25:44.978 --> 25:47.546
Oh, I appreciate that.
You enjoy the peace and quiet.

25:47.937 --> 25:49.548
Take care of each other now.

25:52.463 --> 25:54.727
[OMINOUS MUSIC PLAYING]

26:01.516 --> 26:02.386
Call Stanley.

26:02.517 --> 26:04.388
[MUSIC CONCLUDES]

26:04.519 --> 26:07.783
["THE WEEKEND"
PLAYING OVER RADIO]

26:07.870 --> 26:11.831
<i>♪ Pick me up in your car </i>
<i>Don't care what you're drivin' ♪</i>

26:11.918 --> 26:15.008
<i>♪ But it better be the loud</i>
<i>And fancy type... ♪</i>

26:16.792 --> 26:18.707
DANIEL: Feels like
we're getting close.

26:19.316 --> 26:22.493
Says we should see a mile marker
up here on the right.

26:25.148 --> 26:26.454
ALEX: Is that it?

26:28.891 --> 26:30.980
DANIEL: There it is.
ALEX: There we go.

26:38.205 --> 26:40.033
Is there gonna be a campground?

26:40.468 --> 26:42.426
I mean, it's...

26:43.471 --> 26:44.994
not much of a map, really.

26:50.913 --> 26:52.959
[SONG CONCLUDES]

26:58.094 --> 27:01.402
[PENSIVE MUSIC PLAYING]

27:15.938 --> 27:18.462
[MUSIC CONCLUDES]

27:18.941 --> 27:21.552
[BIRDS CHIRPING]

27:29.169 --> 27:30.561
DANIEL: What do you think?

27:30.736 --> 27:33.216
ALEX: Yeah, it actually
is kinda pretty.

27:33.608 --> 27:34.565
DANIEL: Yeah.

27:35.262 --> 27:37.307
ALEX: I'm just worried about
not being able to take a shower

27:37.394 --> 27:38.395
before the tour tomorrow.

27:39.179 --> 27:40.920
Bet the lake's not that cold.

27:41.007 --> 27:42.312
[SCOFFS] Ha-ha.

27:42.791 --> 27:43.836
It's an art school.

27:44.271 --> 27:45.664
I'm sure you won't be
the only person there

27:45.751 --> 27:48.362
who hasn't showered.
Ew. Okay? That's gross.

27:49.058 --> 27:51.060
No, I'm actually kinda
stressing about it, though.

27:52.845 --> 27:53.759
I hear you.

27:54.890 --> 27:56.718
This part of the trip
was not planned,

27:57.197 --> 27:58.720
but here we are.

27:58.938 --> 27:59.895
Yeah.

27:59.982 --> 28:01.592
Let's try to make
the best of it.

28:01.680 --> 28:03.899
I mean, it's gorgeous.

28:05.292 --> 28:07.294
Yeah. You wanna set up camp?

28:07.860 --> 28:09.339
Yeah. Let's do it.Okay.

28:11.472 --> 28:15.432
[GRUNTS, PANTS]

28:27.270 --> 28:28.271
[CHUCKLES]

28:30.360 --> 28:31.318
[GRUNTS]

28:32.188 --> 28:33.363
[BREATHES DEEPLY]

28:35.583 --> 28:37.890
I'm impressed you still know
how to set this up.

28:37.977 --> 28:38.847
Of course I do.

28:39.239 --> 28:41.067
Did it, like, 10,000 times
when I was little.

28:41.632 --> 28:43.025
Except now
I'm a lot faster at it.

28:43.156 --> 28:44.548
Yeah, because back then,

28:44.635 --> 28:46.725
you insisted
on doing it yourself... [ALEX SCOFFS]

28:46.812 --> 28:48.291
...and you wouldn't
let me help at all.

28:48.422 --> 28:50.816
Those first couple times,
it took me over an hour

28:50.903 --> 28:52.078
and you were just like...

28:52.600 --> 28:54.167
"You're doing great, sweetie."

28:54.254 --> 28:56.560
Meanwhile,
it was completely dark outside.

28:56.647 --> 28:58.301
I respected your determination.

28:58.780 --> 28:59.650
ALEX: Yeah.

28:59.912 --> 29:01.565
DANIEL: Oh, man,
except for that one time.

29:02.088 --> 29:04.046
You remember?
It was raining so hard,

29:04.133 --> 29:05.265
we're getting drenched,

29:05.395 --> 29:07.180
and you still wouldn't
let me help you.

29:07.267 --> 29:08.921
Hey, at least I can talk
about resilience

29:09.008 --> 29:10.792
in my college
application essays now.

29:10.879 --> 29:13.926
Yeah. That was resilient.
ALEX: Yeah.

29:16.493 --> 29:18.931
DANIEL: Yo,
speaking of college essays...

29:21.020 --> 29:23.674
I imagine this school's gonna
wanna see some of your art.

29:24.501 --> 29:25.589
Yeah. Of course.

29:26.547 --> 29:27.461
Could I see some?

29:28.767 --> 29:30.769
I'm taking you there,
shouldn't I at least

29:30.856 --> 29:32.771
have some basic knowledge
of your work?

29:33.336 --> 29:34.729
In case they ask me about it?

29:38.254 --> 29:39.212
Yeah.

29:39.952 --> 29:42.302
Yeah, I know.
I guess you're right. Um...

29:42.781 --> 29:43.999
A couple sketches
I did recently,

29:44.130 --> 29:46.523
and don't judge them
too hard, okay?

29:50.005 --> 29:53.269
[GENTLE MUSIC PLAYING]

29:57.665 --> 29:59.232
So cool.Hmm.

30:01.800 --> 30:03.018
[SCOFFS] They're just sketches.

30:03.105 --> 30:05.586
Yeah, but the style
and the detail

30:05.673 --> 30:06.805
is really something.

30:08.632 --> 30:10.199
Alex, you gotta pursue this.

30:11.679 --> 30:13.333
Are you serious?
Yeah.

30:15.204 --> 30:16.249
Yeah.

30:16.336 --> 30:18.077
You got anything else I can see?

30:19.121 --> 30:21.254
I can show you
a few paintings I've done.

30:27.216 --> 30:28.478
You can just swipe through.

30:31.220 --> 30:34.049
DANIEL: What? Wow.

30:36.182 --> 30:37.574
These are incredible.

30:37.923 --> 30:41.317
[CHUCKLES] I have a whole
portfolio online.

30:41.404 --> 30:43.102
I can show you
once we get service again.

30:43.189 --> 30:44.930
Well, I can't wait
to see it all.

30:45.017 --> 30:46.018
[CHUCKLES]

30:49.064 --> 30:49.935
[SHIVERS]

30:50.022 --> 30:51.110
Cold?
Yeah.

30:52.546 --> 30:54.548
Let's see if we can
find some dry wood.

30:54.635 --> 30:56.202
Make a fire.
Yeah.

30:59.422 --> 31:01.337
[MUSIC CONCLUDES]

31:01.816 --> 31:04.906
[BIRDS CALLING, CHIRPING]

31:06.516 --> 31:07.953
How much more
do you think we need?

31:08.867 --> 31:10.564
Let's hope this stuff burns.

31:10.781 --> 31:12.609
ALEX: Yeah, it's all pretty wet.

31:15.786 --> 31:17.223
[BIRD SCREECHING]

31:18.093 --> 31:18.964
What was that?

31:20.052 --> 31:22.184
DANIEL: I don't know.
Animal, maybe?

31:22.402 --> 31:23.272
Yeah.

31:25.318 --> 31:27.494
[CLACKING IN THE DISTANCE]

31:27.929 --> 31:28.930
Yeah, I heard that.

31:30.889 --> 31:32.934
Like, back in that area, yeah?
Yeah.

31:34.762 --> 31:37.025
Time for a little recon by fire.

31:38.505 --> 31:39.375
[GRUNTS]

31:40.594 --> 31:41.508
[CHUCKLES]

31:43.945 --> 31:45.773
[ROCK THUMPING]

31:45.904 --> 31:47.079
[FOLIAGE SNAPPING]

31:48.428 --> 31:49.559
What was that?

31:50.865 --> 31:52.998
Gotta be, like,
a raccoon or a possum.

31:53.085 --> 31:54.042
ALEX: Huh.

31:54.347 --> 31:56.740
I love that one drawing
with all the faces.

31:57.045 --> 32:00.092
Oh, yeah, I did portraits
of my friends IDs.

32:00.353 --> 32:01.832
DANIEL: Really?
ALEX: [CHUCKLES] Yeah.

32:01.920 --> 32:03.138
DANIEL: That's so cool.

32:04.357 --> 32:08.448
[DISTANT WHISTLING]
[LEAVES RUSTLING]

32:12.321 --> 32:13.279
ALEX: What is it?

32:14.193 --> 32:15.063
It's a person.

32:17.544 --> 32:19.850
[DISTANT WHISTLING]
[LEAVES RUSTLING]

32:24.203 --> 32:25.204
Hey!

32:25.291 --> 32:26.727
[OMINOUS MUSIC PLAYING]

32:26.814 --> 32:27.728
Hello?

32:28.947 --> 32:29.860
We see you.

32:30.122 --> 32:31.427
Oh, I can see you too.

32:31.558 --> 32:33.690
[PROWLER 1 LAUGHING]

32:36.911 --> 32:38.173
Is that your son?

32:42.177 --> 32:43.962
We didn't mean
to spoil your hunt.

32:44.049 --> 32:45.398
We're gonna head back
to the campground.

32:46.094 --> 32:47.487
We don't want any trouble.

32:47.661 --> 32:48.618
[PROWLER 2 SNICKERING]

32:48.705 --> 32:50.359
Move. Don't look back.

32:50.490 --> 32:53.188
PROWLER 2: Hey! Get back here!
Run. Run!

32:53.275 --> 32:55.712
Back to the truck.
[WALKIE TALKIE BEEPS]

32:55.843 --> 32:57.627
PROWLER 2:
They're coming straight to you.

32:57.714 --> 32:59.890
[TRUCK ENGINE REVVING]

33:00.195 --> 33:01.675
They're taking the truck!

33:01.762 --> 33:02.719
Hey!

33:02.850 --> 33:04.983
[THRILLING MUSIC PLAYING]

33:05.070 --> 33:06.549
Hey! Hey!

33:09.422 --> 33:12.033
[GASPS] Dad!
[SCREAMS] No, don't!

33:12.120 --> 33:14.340
[GRUNTS]
[DANIEL GRUNTS]

33:15.123 --> 33:17.256
[GROANS]

33:17.343 --> 33:19.084
[GRUNTS]
[SCREAMS]

33:19.171 --> 33:20.868
[BOTH GRUNT]
[PANTS]

33:21.825 --> 33:23.088
[GRUNTS]
[BONE CRUNCHING]

33:23.262 --> 33:26.265
[SCREAMS, BREATHES HEAVILY]

33:29.529 --> 33:30.443
[GRUNTS]
[GASPS]

33:30.530 --> 33:32.314
Back in the woods, that way!

33:35.970 --> 33:38.625
Stop!
We don't wanna hurt the girl.

33:39.408 --> 33:41.019
[BREATHES HEAVILY]

33:42.020 --> 33:43.586
[WALKIE TALKIE BEEPS]
Jim, Cy.

33:43.673 --> 33:45.849
We got two down, and he's headed
north towards you.

33:45.980 --> 33:47.329
This fucker can fight.

33:48.983 --> 33:51.638
We can hide over there. Run.
[PANTS]

33:51.725 --> 33:54.989
[TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

33:55.120 --> 33:58.210
[PANTS]
[PANTS]

33:59.341 --> 34:01.909
[EXCLAIMS, GASPS, PANTS]
DANIEL: Hey. [SHUSHES]

34:01.996 --> 34:02.997
[ALEX GROANS, MUFFLED]

34:03.954 --> 34:05.478
[WALKIE TALKIE BEEPING]
STANLEY: [OVER RADIO] <i>Jim, Cyrus, are you there?</i>

34:06.522 --> 34:08.698
[WALKIE TALKIE BEEPING]
STANLEY: <i>Jim? Do you have 'em?</i>

34:08.785 --> 34:09.743
[ALEX WHIMPERS]
[WHISPERS] No.

34:11.049 --> 34:12.876
[BRANCHES CRACKING]

34:13.964 --> 34:16.402
[WALKIE TALKIE BEEPING]
STANLEY: <i>Jim, do you copy?</i>

34:16.532 --> 34:17.577
CYRUS: [WHISPERS]
Tell him already.

34:17.664 --> 34:18.665
JIM: [WHISPERS]
Shut the fuck up.

34:19.361 --> 34:20.928
[WALKIE TALKIE BEEPING]
STANLEY: <i>Do you have them or not?</i>

34:20.928 --> 34:21.929
[WALKIE TALKIE BEEPING]

34:22.016 --> 34:24.018
JIM: This is Jim, Stanley.
Uh, no.

34:24.105 --> 34:25.106
[ALEX BREATHES HEAVILY]

34:25.193 --> 34:26.499
JIM: We lost 'em.

34:27.500 --> 34:29.110
STANLEY: <i>What the fuck </i>
<i>do you mean, you lost them?</i>

34:29.197 --> 34:30.503
<i>There's six of you, right?</i>

34:30.677 --> 34:32.331
[WALKIE TALKIE BEEPING]
JIM: Well, they ran away,

34:32.418 --> 34:33.723
but there's nowhere
for them to go.

34:34.159 --> 34:35.682
We'll have 'em soon, I swear.

34:35.856 --> 34:37.336
STANLEY:
<i>Well, you damn well better.</i>

34:37.553 --> 34:39.077
<i>There's too much </i>
<i>at stake for us.</i>

34:39.294 --> 34:41.253
<i>The next fucking thing </i>
<i>I better hear from you</i>

34:41.340 --> 34:43.820
<i>is that you got them, </i>
<i>and you're on your way back.</i>

34:43.907 --> 34:45.344
[WALKIE TALKIE BEEPING]
JIM: We're fucked.

34:46.780 --> 34:51.132
[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC PLAYING]

34:56.355 --> 34:59.532
[BREATHES SHAKILY]
Who... who are those guys?

34:59.662 --> 35:01.011
I have no idea.

35:01.099 --> 35:03.013
ALEX: Do you think they killed
that guy in the corner?

35:04.406 --> 35:05.277
I don't know.

35:05.755 --> 35:07.061
[BREATHES SHAKILY]
DANIEL: We gotta get outta here.

35:07.148 --> 35:08.628
Yeah.
Just wait.

35:10.543 --> 35:14.286
[FLIES BUZZING]

35:24.339 --> 35:27.255
[WHEEZES, BREATHES HEAVILY]

35:27.342 --> 35:31.129
Hey, hey. [SHUSHES]
Just breathe. Just breathe.

35:31.216 --> 35:34.044
I knew... I knew something
was off with that guy

35:34.132 --> 35:35.263
at the gas station.

35:35.655 --> 35:37.787
I knew it, I knew it,
and I didn't tell you.

35:37.874 --> 35:39.006
I should've said something.

35:39.137 --> 35:40.616
I should've said something.
Alex. [SHUSHES]

35:40.703 --> 35:42.792
ALEX: [SOBS] Over and over again
and over and over again.

35:42.879 --> 35:45.012
Look, don't make
any noise, honey. Don't.

35:45.491 --> 35:47.841
Don't.
[SOBS]

35:47.971 --> 35:49.538
[BREATHES HEAVILY]

35:49.625 --> 35:52.541
[GASPS] You're bleeding.
You're bleeding.

35:52.628 --> 35:53.977
You're bleeding.
This is nothing. Look.

35:54.064 --> 35:55.153
It's fine.
They're gonna--

35:55.501 --> 35:56.545
I'm fine. It's nothing.

35:56.719 --> 35:58.112
Okay?
[WHEEZES, BREATHES HEAVILY]

35:58.199 --> 36:00.332
DANIEL: Alex.
Alex, focus. Look at me.

36:00.419 --> 36:02.421
Look at me.
I know you're scared.

36:02.812 --> 36:05.075
I know you're scared,
but I need you focused

36:05.206 --> 36:06.294
if we're gonna get
through this, okay?

36:07.600 --> 36:10.385
Okay. Okay.
DANIEL: So, you gotta trust me.

36:10.603 --> 36:11.908
Okay.
Can you do that?

36:12.213 --> 36:13.954
Yeah. Yeah.
DANIEL: Yeah?

36:14.041 --> 36:17.175
[BREATHES HEAVILY, WHIMPERS]

36:18.611 --> 36:20.090
Do you know where we are?

36:21.831 --> 36:22.963
I'm gonna figure it out.

36:23.093 --> 36:25.313
[PENSIVE MUSIC PLAYING]

36:26.096 --> 36:27.837
[WHIMPERS]
Let's go this way.

36:29.230 --> 36:31.189
[BREATHES SHAKILY, SNIFFLES]

36:32.407 --> 36:33.234
[GROANS]

36:35.889 --> 36:38.196
[WHISPERS] Come on. Stay low.

37:07.573 --> 37:08.661
[SIGHS]

37:16.712 --> 37:21.021
[GASPS, BREATHES SHAKILY]

37:24.807 --> 37:27.070
[BREATHES DEEPLY]

37:33.033 --> 37:35.644
[SOMBER MUSIC PLAYING]

37:35.731 --> 37:37.342
These tablets get the germs out.

37:43.478 --> 37:45.350
[WATER SLOSHING]

37:51.573 --> 37:52.400
Drink.

37:57.623 --> 37:59.973
[GULPS]

38:00.495 --> 38:02.715
I don't understand how
you're not more upset with me.

38:02.802 --> 38:04.543
I made you lock the gun
in the truck.

38:04.630 --> 38:06.240
Alex.
ALEX: I don't even know what I was thinking.

38:06.371 --> 38:08.068
It's my fault that we're
in this situation now, you know?

38:08.155 --> 38:10.462
Alex, don't.
None of this is your fault.

38:10.679 --> 38:11.550
Listen to me.

38:13.247 --> 38:15.728
I have been
in much worse spots than this

38:15.858 --> 38:17.164
over the years.

38:17.295 --> 38:20.298
And I've always
made it through. Always.

38:21.647 --> 38:23.170
And that's when I wasn't trying
to protect the person

38:23.257 --> 38:24.476
I love most in this world.

38:26.347 --> 38:28.306
We are going
to get through this.

38:29.916 --> 38:32.222
I promise.
These guys don't know it yet,

38:32.310 --> 38:33.963
but they messed
with the wrong dad.

38:37.880 --> 38:40.796
[MUSIC CONCLUDES]

38:44.452 --> 38:45.714
ALEX: What? What is it?

38:46.498 --> 38:48.500
DANIEL: You see that gap
between the trees?

38:49.283 --> 38:51.154
There are
no straight lines in nature.

38:52.112 --> 38:53.156
No, there are not.

38:57.726 --> 39:02.470
[ANIMALS CHITTERING]
[BIRDS CALLING]

39:14.961 --> 39:16.963
Railroad tracks
always lead somewhere.

39:19.487 --> 39:21.533
ALEX: Which direction?
This way.

39:22.011 --> 39:25.580
How do you know?
I don't. Just being decisive.

39:32.761 --> 39:35.590
[DISTANT OWL HOOTING]

39:43.032 --> 39:44.120
DANIEL: Get down.

39:50.475 --> 39:51.606
[WHISPERS] Come here.

39:53.478 --> 39:54.827
I think we should go
check that out.

39:54.957 --> 39:56.132
[WHISPERS] No.
No, no, no, no, no.

39:56.306 --> 39:58.308
No, we have to keep going.
I don't wanna go in there.

39:59.048 --> 40:01.181
Honey, there might be something
in there we can use.

40:01.311 --> 40:03.705
I see an antenna.
Could mean radio... weapons.

40:03.836 --> 40:05.664
What are you gonna do,
just walk up and knock?

40:05.794 --> 40:08.144
They're probably hiding
in there, waiting on you.

40:08.231 --> 40:09.668
We can't go anywhere near it.

40:15.021 --> 40:17.110
It might be empty.
[SIGHS]

40:18.024 --> 40:20.505
Either way, we'll make sure
they don't see us coming.

40:20.592 --> 40:21.549
How?

40:27.207 --> 40:28.121
This way.

40:34.910 --> 40:38.174
[VAN ENGINE RUMBLING]

40:43.745 --> 40:49.229
[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC PLAYING]

40:49.621 --> 40:52.101
[BREATHES SHARPLY]

41:08.466 --> 41:10.598
[WHISPERS] I don't hear
any movement. Okay.

41:13.471 --> 41:16.430
Keep a hand on my backpack
and watch our six as we move in.

41:18.171 --> 41:19.694
Okay.
DANIEL: Ready?

41:20.565 --> 41:21.435
Yeah.

41:22.828 --> 41:27.006
[TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

42:08.830 --> 42:12.617
[TENSE MUSIC BUILDS]

42:18.405 --> 42:20.233
[GROWLS, BARKS]
[BOTH GASP]

42:20.494 --> 42:22.365
ALEX: Dad!
[CYRUS SCREAMS, GROANS]

42:22.496 --> 42:24.933
Alex, run!
[ALEX PANTS, GRUNTS]

42:26.282 --> 42:28.720
[DANIEL GRUNTS]
[CYRUS GROANS]

42:31.070 --> 42:32.767
JIM: Come here, you little shit!

42:33.333 --> 42:34.508
Where do you think you're going?

42:34.595 --> 42:36.336
[GRUNTS, PANTS]

42:36.423 --> 42:37.511
[DANIEL PANTS]

42:37.685 --> 42:39.731
ALEX: No!
Alex, run! [GRUNTS]

42:39.905 --> 42:41.471
[SPEAKS INDISTINCTLY, GRUNTS]
[GRUNTS] Let me go!

42:41.559 --> 42:42.864
[GROANS]
[PROWLERS GRUNT]

42:43.038 --> 42:44.953
ANGUS: Come here!
[GROANS]

42:45.127 --> 42:47.303
[ALEX SCREAMS]
Damn it, just frickin'...

42:47.869 --> 42:50.350
[GRUNTS]
[GROANS]

42:50.437 --> 42:52.657
[BOTH GRUNT]
Stop squirming! God!

42:52.787 --> 42:54.789
[BOTH GRUNT]

42:54.876 --> 42:55.834
[NICKY GROANS]

42:56.530 --> 42:59.925
[CHOKES] Stop fucking moving!
[GRUNTS] ALEX: [GRUNTS] Dad!

43:00.795 --> 43:01.840
[DANIEL GRUNTS]
[ANGUS GROANS]

43:02.057 --> 43:04.190
[GRUNTS]
[SCREAMS, GRUNTS]

43:05.408 --> 43:07.323
[ALEX GRUNTS]
[GASPS, CHOKES]

43:07.410 --> 43:09.674
GAR: No! [SCREAMS]
[DANIEL GROANS]

43:10.413 --> 43:11.414
No!

43:11.589 --> 43:14.026
[DANIEL GROANS]
[GRUNTS]

43:15.375 --> 43:18.073
[GAR GRUNTS]
[GRUNTS]

43:18.204 --> 43:21.076
[GROANS, PANTS]
[GRUNTS]

43:21.207 --> 43:24.079
I'm gonna rip
your fucking heart out! [GRUNTS]

43:24.210 --> 43:27.082
[PANTS] Dad! No!
[GAR GRUNTS]

43:27.996 --> 43:30.042
[ALEX GRUNTS]

43:30.259 --> 43:32.392
[DANIEL GRUNTS]

43:32.566 --> 43:35.351
[GRUNTS]
[GROANS]

43:35.482 --> 43:36.744
ALEX: Dad! No!

43:36.831 --> 43:39.399
[DOG BARKING]

43:41.880 --> 43:43.838
ALEX: Dad!
[GRUNTS, GROANS]

43:44.230 --> 43:45.535
Let's go!
[PANTS]

43:47.755 --> 43:48.800
[GRUNTS]

43:48.974 --> 43:50.062
[MUSIC CONCLUDES]

43:54.414 --> 43:57.896
[PANTS][PANTS, GRUNTS]

43:58.026 --> 43:59.201
Alex!
[GROANS]

43:59.375 --> 44:03.031
Alex, are you okay, honey?
My ankle. [WHIMPERS]

44:03.597 --> 44:05.555
We... we killed
that guy, and I...

44:05.643 --> 44:08.297
and I helped you and his knife
was like, right there.

44:08.384 --> 44:09.777
[SHUSHES]
And there was so much blood.

44:09.864 --> 44:11.431
[SOBS] I was on his shoulder.
Alex, Alex, sweetheart.

44:12.127 --> 44:15.435
You did what you had to do.
It's us or them. Okay?

44:15.522 --> 44:17.306
Why are they trying to take me?
I don't know.

44:17.393 --> 44:18.612
I don't understand.
I don't know.

44:18.743 --> 44:20.005
All right, baby,
come here, come here.

44:20.135 --> 44:22.050
I know, but I got you.
[LILY BREATHES HEAVILY]

44:22.355 --> 44:24.531
Okay? Now,
do you think you can walk?

44:25.924 --> 44:28.100
Huh?
I think so.

44:28.187 --> 44:29.492
Okay, 'cause we gotta
get moving.

44:30.493 --> 44:34.497
All right, let me help you up.
[PANTS, GROANS]

44:35.020 --> 44:37.326
All right, let's go,
let's go, let's go.

44:39.938 --> 44:41.853
[BREATHES HEAVILY, GROANS]

44:43.419 --> 44:45.421
Fuck.
We need help.

44:45.639 --> 44:46.771
We should go back and get help.

44:46.901 --> 44:49.121
We're not going nowhere
without that girl.

44:49.556 --> 44:50.688
Keep your shit together.

44:51.732 --> 44:52.907
Nicky's dead, Angus.

44:53.473 --> 44:55.562
I can fucking see that, Gar.

44:58.696 --> 45:01.176
Do you wanna be the one
to go back to tell Stanley

45:01.263 --> 45:02.569
that Nicky's dead?

45:02.917 --> 45:04.266
And we didn't get the girl?

45:05.006 --> 45:06.747
How do you think he's
going to react, huh?

45:09.054 --> 45:12.274
JIM: Let's go, boys.
We don't got all night.

45:13.275 --> 45:14.363
What about Nicky?

45:14.450 --> 45:15.800
JIM: We'll come back
for him later.

45:17.279 --> 45:18.454
Fuck.

45:19.368 --> 45:23.198
[BIRDS CHIRPING]

45:30.858 --> 45:31.946
How's that ankle?

45:32.033 --> 45:33.687
Yeah, it's okay.

45:46.395 --> 45:47.875
DANIEL:
I think we should rest that leg.

45:48.833 --> 45:50.182
ALEX: I can keep going.

45:50.399 --> 45:51.531
DANIEL: If we don't rest,

45:51.661 --> 45:53.054
we make ourselves
more vulnerable.

45:53.185 --> 45:57.580
[ALEX PANTS]

46:01.584 --> 46:03.543
DANIEL: Let's check out
this spot. It looks good.

46:04.109 --> 46:05.371
All right, let me
take a quick look.

46:05.501 --> 46:06.502
ALEX: Okay.

46:17.818 --> 46:18.993
Nice.

46:21.517 --> 46:22.649
This is perfect.

46:23.128 --> 46:25.217
You can see or hear
anyone coming.

46:26.435 --> 46:28.350
They won't be able to
see us once it gets dark.

46:34.835 --> 46:36.010
Okay.

46:39.884 --> 46:41.929
You brought all that
for college visits?

46:44.062 --> 46:47.326
It's a habit.
Never hurts to be prepared.

46:49.415 --> 46:54.246
Look. I got your favorite.
Maple pork sausage patty.

46:55.551 --> 46:57.815
Mm. Yummy. [CHUCKLES SOFTLY]

47:04.691 --> 47:05.692
DANIEL:
Didn't think I'd be eating

47:05.779 --> 47:07.389
another one of these
for a while.

47:20.011 --> 47:22.535
What's the real reason
you left the army so suddenly?

47:23.144 --> 47:24.842
Obviously, you loved it.

47:25.059 --> 47:27.148
Mom and I thought you were
gonna do another ten years.

47:34.590 --> 47:35.853
Truth is...

47:37.767 --> 47:39.595
I got in a fistfight
with my C.O.

47:40.988 --> 47:42.033
What happened?

47:48.300 --> 47:50.345
My last op went kinda sideways.

47:51.738 --> 47:54.219
We were just going back
to evacuate some local personnel

47:54.349 --> 47:55.611
we worked with.

47:57.135 --> 48:00.051
But people found out.
And it was chaos.

48:00.138 --> 48:02.183
Just so many people
trying to escape.

48:02.967 --> 48:04.882
Families. Kids.

48:08.842 --> 48:10.757
There was one guy who
tried to hand me his baby

48:10.844 --> 48:12.715
across the barbed wire
before we took off.

48:12.933 --> 48:15.414
Yeah, just begging me
to take her.

48:17.677 --> 48:20.767
And I tried to.
My C.O. got pissed.

48:21.768 --> 48:23.161
He ordered me to leave her.

48:23.248 --> 48:25.076
Said this is not
why we're here.

48:26.729 --> 48:29.254
When I refused,
he got in my face.

48:31.082 --> 48:32.300
And I lost it.

48:37.175 --> 48:38.219
So...

48:39.090 --> 48:41.831
My retirement wasn't
exactly voluntary.

48:44.747 --> 48:45.923
And the baby?

48:51.058 --> 48:52.364
She didn't make it outta there.

48:55.454 --> 48:56.846
I'm sorry, Dad.

48:58.239 --> 49:04.071
[SOMBER MUSIC PLAYING]

49:07.770 --> 49:09.381
ALEX: Can I ask you
one more thing?

49:09.903 --> 49:10.991
Sure.

49:12.471 --> 49:14.777
Did you win the fight
with your C.O.?

49:15.256 --> 49:16.823
Oh, I whooped his ass.

49:16.997 --> 49:18.651
[CHUCKLES]
DANIEL: Real good.

49:19.434 --> 49:20.609
ALEX: Good.

49:22.437 --> 49:24.396
I think I'm done. [CHUCKLES]

49:26.267 --> 49:27.399
DANIEL: Alex.

49:29.053 --> 49:30.532
When I was over there,

49:30.663 --> 49:32.360
it put me
in a certain headspace.

49:34.145 --> 49:36.103
I didn't know
how to be that guy...

49:37.583 --> 49:39.846
and then hop on the phone
with you and be a dad.

49:43.067 --> 49:44.677
But I should've found a way.

49:48.986 --> 49:50.161
And I'm sorry.

49:52.206 --> 49:54.513
Yeah. Thank you.

49:56.341 --> 49:58.560
And I know. I know.

50:04.436 --> 50:06.177
God, I'm tired.

50:06.307 --> 50:08.657
DANIEL: Yeah?
Yeah. It's getting cold.

50:08.788 --> 50:09.963
DANIEL: All right. Here.

50:12.922 --> 50:14.533
You can use this.
ALEX: Thank you.

50:17.188 --> 50:20.756
I'll come up there
to keep you warm.

50:26.545 --> 50:27.937
Here. Come here.

50:32.594 --> 50:36.076
I might just close my eyes
for a few minutes.

50:36.294 --> 50:37.425
Yeah, go ahead.

50:39.949 --> 50:41.212
I'll stay on watch.

50:52.397 --> 50:56.227
[CRICKETS CHIRPING]

50:56.662 --> 51:01.014
[BIRDS CHIRPING]

51:14.854 --> 51:16.421
I need to go to the bathroom.

51:17.639 --> 51:19.076
Yeah?
Yeah.

51:35.962 --> 51:37.529
My ankle feels better.

51:37.833 --> 51:39.705
Well, that's great.
Yeah.

51:39.966 --> 51:41.272
I'll be right back.

51:41.489 --> 51:43.100
Don't go far.
Yeah.

51:59.377 --> 52:01.509
Now, you two stay close.
I'm going to go up top

52:01.640 --> 52:02.858
and I'll meet you
by the north fork.

52:02.945 --> 52:04.947
And for the love of God,
shut the fuck up.

52:05.252 --> 52:08.647
I can hear you over a mile away.
Come on, come on, come on.

52:08.734 --> 52:11.432
Follow me.
I told you to shut the fuck up!

52:12.520 --> 52:14.305
Yeah, just keep your mouth shut.

52:23.792 --> 52:26.273
Ah!
[GRUNTS]

52:27.448 --> 52:32.453
[BOTH GRUNT]

52:34.890 --> 52:37.806
[BOTH GRUNT]

52:39.068 --> 52:40.766
[CYRUS WHISPERS] Take a break.

52:40.853 --> 52:42.768
[SHUSHES]

52:43.377 --> 52:47.076
[DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYING]

52:47.207 --> 52:49.296
[YELPS]

52:55.955 --> 52:57.348
Dad, I found her.

